gomodel:SYNGO_950  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Knockdown of FLNA causes a reduction in spine density, increase in spine length and decrease in spine width, indicating a less mature spine morphology. Therefore I assigned the GO term modification of postsynaptic structure.. Experimental description: from main text: \"We co-transfected MHNs with tdT together with scr or Flna-specific shRNA (shFlna) alone or together with shPhd2.\"\n\nn.b. MHN stands for mouse hippocampal neurons" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6153-3586" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2666-0758" ;
